### Setup

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/{{ github_repo }}.git
cd {{ package_name }}

# Setup development environment
make setup

# Run tests
make test

# See all available commands
make help
```

### Building Native Libraries

Native libraries are pre-built and downloaded automatically via build hooks.
If you need to build them locally:

```bash
# Build for current platform
make build ARGS="<platform>"

# Examples:
make build ARGS="macos --arch arm64"
make build ARGS="linux --arch x86_64"
make build ARGS="android --abi arm64-v8a"
```

### Regenerating FFI Bindings

After modifying header files:

```bash
make regen
```

